    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1037"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1037">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EAC1"
                    >EAC</gloss>/7–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1037<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-24">24 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Tripartite Conference, Babelsberg, top secret from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> serial number 44360. Sent the Secretary
                    Babelsberg top secret from <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> and to
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 7434, July 24, <gloss
                        target="#t_Comea1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Comea</hi>
                    </gloss> 340.</p>
                <p>Your <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 241 July 23<note n="1" xml:id="d1037fn1">See <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_321">p. 321</ref>.</note> received.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> met last night to complete two outstanding
                    documents. …<note n="2" xml:id="d1037fn2">For the passage omitted here, see <ref
                            target="#d1031">document No. 1031</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Saksin</persName> stated his Government approved
                    additional requirements agreement with last part of title reading in translation
                    “certain additional requirements to Germany”. Original English title read
                    “certain additional requirements to be imposed on Germany”. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGF1">Saksin</persName> insisted title he [was] authorized to
                    accept could not be translated as in English version and he would have to obtain
                    new instructions in order to accept that wording. Apparently discrepancy arose
                    at time Soviet delegation originally telegraphed proposed title to Soviet
                    Government. <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Saksin</persName> claimed his delgation
                    was not aware at that time that English and French versions contained phrase “to
                    be imposed”. He stated he would telegraph for new instructions. Perhaps
                        <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> could see <persName
                        corresp="#p_G10">Gousev</persName> and expedite necessary instructions to
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Saksin</persName>.<note n="3" xml:id="d1037fn3"
                        >For <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName>’ reply to this message,
                        following a conversation at the Berlin Conference between <persName
                            corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_GFT1"
                            >Gusev</persName>, see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_407">p. 407</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
